                        <item xml:id="e1">- Running titles are finely written between two lines of
                           black and red dots, in the middle of 
 the upper margin of the
                           incipit folio for each Gospel book, and in the first recto-folio of each
                           quire. 
 - Titles of the chapters are written in the upper margins in
                           reddish brown ink, in a crude secondary hand, and encircled with thin
                           lines.
 - A record has been washed out: <locus target="#202r">202r</locus>.
 - Pen trial ፈቲነ፡ ብርኢ፡ ዘጸሐፍዋ፡ ሊቃውቲ: <locus target="#202va">202va</locus>.</item>
