               <provenance>Takla Māryām is mentioned in the postscripts
                     to the Gospels (62vb, 98va, 155rb and 201vb).
                     Other persons are mentioned in the headings of the Gospels (Gabra Māryām, Kǝfla
                     Māryām and Zarʾa Buruk), written in a different hand in reddish-brown ink,
                     whereas the name of Takla Māryām has been partly erased. Zarʾa Buruk (s. Additio 1). The Ms. might
                     have been in the library of Mäqdäla Madḫāne ʿĀlam.</provenance></history>
